
app.post('/persons'): This route is used to create a new person document. It takes the request body, parses it and adds it to the database

app.get('/persons') : this route is used to display all of the persons in the collection.

app.get('/persons/:id'): This route fetches a single document from the database. The Id of the fetched person is specified in the params

app.put('/persons/:id'): This route is used to edit a single document whose ID is specified from the collection. The changes to be edited are passed as json from the request body

app.delete('/persons/:id'): This route deletes a single document from the collection. 

app.get('*'): this is the default route that shows an error page when all other route are not hit